HEADWORD: Noetical
<hw>No*et"ic*al</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/, fr. <?/ to perceive,
<?/ mind, intellect.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to the intellect;
intellectual.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I would employ the word <qex>noetic</qex> to express all those
cognitions which originate in the mind itself.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

